summary: This document provides detailed information on how to view aircraft records, including the types of files contained on a CD Rom, the sequence of document display, and the types of documents related to aircraft airworthiness and registration. It emphasizes the organization and retrieval of aircraft records for legal and administrative purposes.
keyFacts: The document outlines the structure and content of aircraft records available on CD Rom.
It describes the types of files included, such as Airworthiness, Registration, and Suspense files.
The document explains the numbering system used for documents and pages within the aircraft records.
